<typeStatus box="[1338,1428,1270,1294]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">syntype</typeStatus>
) with the following data: ‘Nilgiri Hills; Lovedale (T. V. Campbell)’. One specimen each of 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1352,1307,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[1222,1236,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1254,1352,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilgiriensis">
<emphasis box="[1415,1429,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,277,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">nilgiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered 
<typeStatus box="[452,550,1343,1367]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">syntypes</typeStatus>
as they have both 
<collectionCode box="[757,841,1343,1366]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">BMNH</collectionCode>
registration labels dated before their publication date and original data labels. The remaining specimens listed under ‘Other material examined’ are topotypical but we cannot be sure of their status (see Material and Methods). This species and 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1166,1413,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotata">
<emphasis box="[992,1006,1415,1438]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1020,1166,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">quadrinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by their relatively pale dorsum (particularly females) but the former is larger and the genitalia is distinctly different. The aedeagal shaft of 
<taxonomicName box="[420,551,1487,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[420,551,1487,1510]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[617,742,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis box="[617,742,1486,1510]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar in having spicules and serrated lateral margins, however, they differ in the curvature of the shaft in lateral view and shape in caudal view (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1277,1436,1522,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 113–119" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[259,1367,218,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[189,1409,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 113–119. Penthimia fraterna Distant. 113. Male pygofer, lateral view; 114. Subgenital plate and part of valve, ventral view; 115. Style, lateral view; 116. Apical apophysis of style, lateral view; 117. Connective, dorsal view; 118. Aedeagus, lateral view; 119. Aedeagal shaft, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135496/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 118, 119</figureCitation>
with 137, 138). Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1918" box="[440,593,1557,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilgiriensis">
<emphasis box="[440,593,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. nilgiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described first by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant" box="[850,1011,1557,1582]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Distant, W. L. (1918) Rhynchota- Homoptera: Appendix. Heteroptera: Addenda. In: Shipley, A. E. &amp; Marshall, G. A. K. (Eds.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Vol. 7. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. 1 - viii + 1 - 210." type="book chapter" year="1918">Distant (1918)</bibRefCitation>
we prefer to use the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1436,1559,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[1311,1436,1559,1582]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its 
<typeStatus box="[215,263,1595,1619]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
is a male
</paragraph>
